⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of DETERRENCE
node DET · DET · ⟦DETERRENCE:DET:4839f5⟧

WHO   — DETERRENCE — a polemos sphere
WHAT  — The strangest victory is the war that never happens. Deterrence is the art of making an attack so costly that no one starts it — of winning by convincing the other side they cannot win. In the nuclear age it became a global, permanent standoff: mutual assured destruction, a peace held in place by the credible promise of annihilation.
WHERE — a sphere of the field of conflict  Framework inputs: value; exchange; rivalry; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The strangest victory is the war that never happens. Deterrence is the art of making an attack so costly that no one starts it — of winning by convincing the other side they cannot win. In the nuclear age it became a global, permanent standoff: mutual assured destruction, a peace held in place by the credible promise of annihilation.
